<p>Along with his success as a musician, he also starred in his own NBC variety show, The Mac Davis Show, from 1974 to 1976, which lead to his acting career.</p>

<p>He made his feature film debut in the 1974 film North Dallas Forty, along with Cheaper to Keep Her and The Sting II.</p>

<p>He also appeared in several TV movies and, most recently he starred in 2008's Beer For My Horses and 2017's Where The Fast Lane Ends.</p>

